{
  "stem": "10162.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At my trial.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was just a lesson for me that stuck for the rest of my life with Hungary, that you're not supposed to say this because it's not taken the way you, you, you give it.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and the background for this is, of course, the anti-Semitism that permeated the Stalins-- Stalinstad communism.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You probably remember, also, you know, the Jewish doctors trials.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was horrendous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We all knew that these are trumped-up charges and far-fetched.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it started in Russia, and then it came in S-- the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then it was coming toward Hungary, also.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So, of course, communism is really like a religion and doesn't tolerate any other religions, but least of all it tolerated Jewis-- Jewishness.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were not supposed to-- just not supposed to say anything about that ever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, which also adds another dimension of what we went through-- Hungarian Jews or Czech Jews or Polish Jews who went back for one reason or the other.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because if you-- those who came to the United States or to France or Switzerland or to a free Western type-- style democracy were able to pick up the pieces and make a life for themselves.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But like we went from, from one thing into the other, one, one, one terrible thing into the other.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to live a lie for so many years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, anyway, I was in this marriage, and I, I just knew that this, this is-- this cannot last.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's something.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have to find some kind of a solution.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
